<div id="review_122011885" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/122011885" />
    <a title="Cecilia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/95738-cecilia"><img alt="Cecilia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1539017383p2/95738.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/122011885?book_show_action=true">Sep 16, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cecilia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cecilia" href="/user/show/95738-cecilia">Cecilia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/95738-cecilia?shelf=wednight-bkclb">wednight-bkclb</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/95738-cecilia?shelf=kindle">kindle</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/95738-cecilia?shelf=read-2011">read-2011</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/95738-cecilia?shelf=suspense-thriller">suspense-thriller</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer122011885" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18321182665419244280">LOVED this book. The language was so lyrical and it pulled me through even though in the beginning I did not know where I was going.<br/><br/>It was almost like being given the stings of a tapestry and weaving an amazingly complex and ever changing pattern. The picture is there in your mind, and you have an idea of how it will present itself, but only to discover you are looking at it from the wrong end... or side... or upside down. <br/><br/>It almost had a <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/7751.Tennessee_Williams' title='Tennessee Williams' rel='nofollow noopener'>Tennessee Williams</a>, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/161915.Suddenly_Last_Summer' title='Suddenly Last Summer by Tennessee Williams' rel='nofollow noopener'>Suddenly Last Summer</a> feel. Only with </span>
  <span id="freeText18321182665419244280" style="display:none">LOVED this book. The language was so lyrical and it pulled me through even though in the beginning I did not know where I was going.<br /><br />It was almost like being given the stings of a tapestry and weaving an amazingly complex and ever changing pattern. The picture is there in your mind, and you have an idea of how it will present itself, but only to discover you are looking at it from the wrong end... or side... or upside down. <br /><br />It almost had a <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/7751.Tennessee_Williams" title="Tennessee Williams" rel="nofollow noopener">Tennessee Williams</a>, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/161915.Suddenly_Last_Summer" title="Suddenly Last Summer by Tennessee Williams" rel="nofollow noopener">Suddenly Last Summer</a> feel. Only with Bougainvillaea not Calla Lilies.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18321182665419244280" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


