<div id="review_938769431" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/938769431" />
    <a title="Liz Nix" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30775380-liz-nix"><img alt="Liz Nix" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1481994604p2/30775380.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/938769431?book_show_action=true">May 15, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Liz Nix" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Liz Nix" href="/user/show/30775380-liz-nix">Liz Nix</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer938769431" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1266622572064446749">There is no way to properly describe this book and why it is interesting. You just have to read the whole thing. <br/><br/>I am a fair-weather avid reader (I get excited about reading and discussing books for a while and then move on to another hobby) and I&apos;m glad I read this while in an avid phase. It was a bit long and drawn out in the middle, but I think it all came together so well at the end. <br/><br/>The writing style was slow, but pretty (forgive me, I&apos;m no literary genius). I like books that read a little </span>
  <span id="freeText1266622572064446749" style="display:none">There is no way to properly describe this book and why it is interesting. You just have to read the whole thing. <br /><br />I am a fair-weather avid reader (I get excited about reading and discussing books for a while and then move on to another hobby) and I'm glad I read this while in an avid phase. It was a bit long and drawn out in the middle, but I think it all came together so well at the end. <br /><br />The writing style was slow, but pretty (forgive me, I'm no literary genius). I like books that read a little like poetry but keep the story moving. The characters were very well developed. It needs to be said that this is exactly my kind of book. Secrets, intrigue, betrayal, a little love, but not the sappy kind. If that's not your cup of tea, than I wouldn't bother. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1266622572064446749" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


